<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbb38be0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s1997d"><num value="1997d">§ 1997d.</num><heading> Prohibition of retaliation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No person reporting conditions which may constitute a violation under this subchapter shall be subjected to retaliation in any manner for so reporting.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbb38be1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/247/s6">Pub. L. 96–247, § 6</ref>, <date date="1980-05-23">May 23, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/352">94 Stat. 352</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
